name: Almonds
properties: Rich in vitamin E, a powerful antioxidant, prevents signs of aging caused by free radicals.

name: Green Tea
properties: Since green tea contains polyphenols, making it an antioxidant and an anti-inflammatory. It’s great for healing blemishes and scars, flushes out toxins, and also keeps skin supple. The vitamin K in green tea helps lighten dark circles under the eyes.

name: Kale
properties: Rich in vitamin A, which is an antioxidant and promotes healthy skin cell. Applying kale topically helps diminish the visibility of bruises, scars, stretch marks.

name: Walnut
properties: Walnuts help in collagen production because they are high in omega-3 fatty acids. Collagen, it’s a protein that helps improve the skin’s elasticity, preventing sagging and ultimately leaving your skin plump and youthful.

name: Tomato
properties: Tomatoes are rich in lycopene, a potent antioxidant to protect skin from UV damage.

name: Watermelon
properties: High concentration of water in watermelon can actually reduce the water retention that leads to puffiness around the eyes.

name: Salmon
properties: Salmon is rich in antioxidants that calm inflammation. The free fatty acids serve as building blocks for healthy skin cells.

name: Sunflower Seeds
properties: Sunflower seeds are an excellent source of nutrients, including vitamin E, which is an important antioxidant for the skin.

name: Sweet Potato
properties: Sweet potatoes are an excellent source of beta-carotene, which acts as a natural sunblock and may protect your skin from sun damage.
